snippet.textDisplay:
What is wrong with people? Why can't they just mind their own buisness and not tell others what to do or how to look?
I was bullied for my weight from first class and until the end of 9:th year (wich is the "ground-years" in Sweden) and I wasn't accually that big, but every one made me feel that way. I then lost a lot of weight by working with horses. But after an accident (and several surgerys) I gained sooo much weight that I became obese.
My body started hurting a lot, and about 24 years after the accident I finally gave in and had gastric bypass.
I have now lost 25 kilos (started at 101,6 kg) and everyone tells me how good I look _now_.
Well... THANKS for calling me ugly before the surgery... :P Even though you didn't actually say that then... When you are telling me how good I look now after weightloss... you are saying that I was ugly before....

The thing is though, I never did this to look good. I did it because my knees, ankles and hips started to hurt after carrying that weight around for so long.
I rather hear that I look healthy now, instead of "looking good" or "looking skinny" (or the worst "so slim and beautiful").

I am sorry that you have to read those comments Shane, and everybody else that have to go trough that.
Please remember that you are beautiful from the inside out - and not just skin deep.

snippet.textDisplay: I’m usually too shy to post comments but I feel like I need to.  Shane, I’ve been watching your videos for 10+ years.  I’ve always enjoyed your sense of humor and your “realness”. I’m sure if most people would acquire the level of success you have, it would go to their heads.  From what I’ve watched over the years, you’ve stayed true to yourself.  Another big reason I’ve stayed a loyal viewer is because it’s been nice to know there’s someone else out there that I can relate to in regards to weight struggles.  I’ve been plus size my entire life and was relentlessly bullied for it.  Even to this day as an adult, I  still have to deal with judgmental jerks that don’t know my life.  It sucks living day to day feeling like I should apologize for how I look when I’m just trying to live my best life.  People are mean and there’s nothing we can do to change it.  It’s the sad truth “we can’t control people’s actions, we can only control how we react”.  Thank you for showing me it’s ok to get sad and upset but also showing all of us that we can rise above it.  You are an inspiration and I love you even more since finding out you have a bling obsession that rivals my own.
